<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Something to think about:<p>

one or two int or wisdom can never hurt -- but over time, the prices you pay for your supplies really add up.  do yourself a favor and get some charisma gear and you'll also save money over time.<p>

Right now I'd suggest making class 2 arrows ...small nock, parabolic fletch, wood shaft and field point (trivial at 56) and selling them at 1pp per stack.  You more than double your money and high lvl rangers will usually buy huge quantities of arrows from you.  I've gotten orders for 8-12 stacks at a time.  <br>
My best sellers have been the 3 damage, 150 range arrows and I try to sell them at 20pp per 100.<p>

You won't make huge amounts of money but you'll be able to pay for your fletching.  As for the bow, heheh, I prefer making my own bows and arrows to kill with.  Just make the best one that you can and keep fletching<img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/Wilk.gif" border="0" align="middle"><p>

Oh yeah, don't take anything in trade unless it's something you will use.  Otherwise you end up just being another merchant in the Commons and that takes  a lot of time.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
